DataElement.preferredName: Ribonucleic Acid Microarray Analysis Report Whole Average Signal java.lang.Double
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A nucleic acid molecule similar to DNA but containing ribose rather than deoxyribose. RNA is formed upon a DNA template. There are several classes of RNA molecules. They play crucial roles in protein synthesis and other cell activities. (MedicineNet.com):Analysis using microarray technology (e.g., cDNA arrays to see gene expression or protein microarrays to profile the pattern of proteins).:A short textual account; having provided a short account._Including all components without exception; being one unit or constituting the full amount or extent or duration; complete.:A statistical calculation describing the central tendency of a set of numbers; used to interpret quantitative data.:A detectable physical quantity or impulse (e.g., voltage, current, or magnetic field strength)._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).

Analysis using microarray technology (e.g., cDNA arrays to see gene expression or protein microarrays to profile the pattern of proteins).
